__e: No books. No, it has to be a book, Dwight.
I say we put a pickaxe in his head and the dead girl's and be done with it.
He taught me there ain't no tree that could best a axe in the right hands, no matter how strong its trunk, no matter how long it's been there.
I shouldn't have sent my brothers after you with knives and axes.
